Adult.description: The Western Screech-Owl looks very similar but has little or no range overlap with the Eastern Screech-Owl. Vocalizations differ: Western has an accelerating series of hoots, while Eastern has a descending whinny.
Northern Saw-whet Owls are slightly smaller than Eastern Screech-Owls and lack ear tufts. They also have less intricately barred underparts.
